definitions.definition: A relationship of mutual benefit , especially among different species.
The close and long-term relationship or interaction between two or more different species in which at least one of the organisms benefit.

subdefinitions.definition: The close and long-tern relationship or interaction between two or more different species in which all organisms benefit; mutualism .
examples: Bees and flowers display symbiosis . The bees get nectar and the flowers get pollinated

definitions.definition: The state of people of different types, races, cultures, communities, etc., living together.
The occurrence of two different or opposing things in the same time and place.
